HIMSELF JUSTICE.

23:40.377 --> 23:44.462
THE ACTOR THAT PLAYED YOU
WASN'T WORTH A DARN.

23:44.548 --> 23:46.505
BUT THAT THERE GARRITY

23:46.592 --> 23:49.425
SURE CAN DO A JOB
OF RESURRECTING.

23:49.470 --> 23:52.508
I CAN'T WAIT TO GET
BACK INTO TOWN.

23:52.598 --> 23:56.182
I'VE GOT A LOT OF DRINKING
TO CATCH UP WITH.

23:56.268 --> 23:58.259
THERE'S A YELLOW SKUNK
OF A SHERIFF

23:58.312 --> 24:00.178
I AIM TO SETTLE
A SCORE WITH, TOO.

24:00.272 --> 24:02.013
AND THERE'S
A LITTLE PIPSQUEAK

24:02.107 --> 24:04.519
OF A SOT JUST WAITING
TO GET HIS ARM BROKE

24:04.610 --> 24:06.692
AND I'M JUST THE GAL
THAT CAN DO IT

24:06.779 --> 24:08.816
OR MY NAME
AIN'T ZELDA GOOBERMAN.

24:08.906 --> 24:11.614
<i>(narrator) EXIT MR. GARRITY,
A WOULD-BE CHARLATAN,</i>

24:11.700 --> 24:13.532
<i>A MAKE-BELIEVE CON MAN</i>

24:13.619 --> 24:16.486
<i>AND A SAD MISJUDGER
OF HIS OWN TALENTS.</i>

24:16.580 --> 24:19.493
<i>RESPECTFULLY SUBMITTED
FROM AN EMPTY CEMETERY</i>

24:19.583 --> 24:21.620
<i>ON A DARK HILLSIDE</i>

24:21.669 --> 24:24.377
<i>THAT IS ONE OF THE SLOPES
LEADING TO THE TWILIGHT ZONE.</i>

24:27.591 --> 24:29.628
<i>(male presenter)
AND NOW, MR. SERLING.</i>

24:29.718 --> 24:31.629
THE SUBJECT NEXT TIME
IS AUTOMATION.

24:31.720 --> 24:33.176
OUR AREA OF CONCERN:

24:33.263 --> 24:35.220
THE REPLACEMENT OF MEN
BY MACHINES.

24:35.307 --> 24:37.548
IT HAPPENS TO BE NOT ONLY A
CURRENT INDUSTRIAL PHENOMENON

24:37.643 --> 24:39.475
BUT POTENTIALLY
A SIZABLE CAN OF PEAS,

24:39.561 --> 24:40.972
